values: A piece of my tooth chipped off. I think it has something to do with fighting two doods, whilst being drunk off my keister.  Damn that was a good Birthday.
You've made your bed, now lie in it, and shut the fuck up!

This Friday is my twin sister's wedding. She's having it in Boston. This should be a very interesting day for me.  My father will be there, along with his whore of a wife. Both I haven't seen or spoken to in about 6 years. There's still a lot of animosity between us.

I just think the whole wedding is a big joke, and I'm not the only one.

At least it's open bar all night.

Well, I've been struck twice. After I finished my overnight 12 hour shift, I went to go get my slashed tire replaced. I arrived to my apt, to find the front door unlocked. As I enter MY domain, I notice that two laptops are missing (mine, and Chucky's). Both which were gifts from my mother. I notice my closet light on, which I never leave on. I look over to my stereo unit, and notice that my Dell Digital Jukebox is missing, which again was a gift from my mother. I spoke to Chuck, and he wasn't home at all. I also noticed that Chucks camcorder was missing as well. 

So, we were officially robbed. I called the fuzz, made a report. Called my insurance company, thank god I had renters insurance!! (Thanks mom for bugging me to get it). So, my week has pretty much SUCKED!!!

I have my camping trip next weekend, and I just hope against hope, that is doesn't rain on my parade! FUCK I NEED A VACATION!!! 

So, I won't be able to access my myspace, LJ or AOL for awhile. So, if you need to get ahold of me. Please call my cell. 603-547-5170. DAMN YOU LIFE! DAMN YOU TO HELL!!!

The show in Worcester was great, the slashed tire after the show was even better. 
Thanks people of Worcester,you are beautiful. SCUM!

Camping trip June 16th. So far the list includes, Myself,Chucky Ballz,The Bishop Don The Magic Juan, Big Poppa John, Bryan Dean, hopefully Joey Cogs, and Bob Knob. I'm sure the list will grow. 

The camping trip will be at Lafayette Campgound, in Franconia Notch,NH. It's a beautiful place, and I reserved two sweet sites. Both are by the river. This will be a big bro-fest, I wonder how long everyone will last without their cell phones? Mead,Brendan and Josh, if you read this you're more than welcome to come along. Actually, I hope you do!
Fucking drama. Petty bullshit. I just can't win. Damn it.

My birthday is Jan 19th. But, I'm planning to do a little celebrating this weekend. Probably Friday or Saturday depending on peoples schedules. All are welcome. Just let me know if you need directions to my pad. Most likely it will be the traditonal Nashua Bar Crawl.
My face hurts. I feel like a sideshow freak at the carnival. People stare at me, like I'm the elephant man.

Dear Santa...

Dear Santa,

This year I've been busy!

In June I broke 's X-Box (-12 points). In July I caught a purse-snatcher who stole 's purse (30 points). In May I set 's puppy on fire (-66 points). In August I pulled 's hair (-5 points). Last Friday I had a shoot-out with rival gang lords on the 5 near LA (-76 points).

Overall, I've been naughty (-129 points). For Christmas I deserve a lump of coal!

Sincerely,
2livejew

Write your letter to Santa! Enter your LJ username:

Party in D.C. for New Years. It's going to be a raging good time. I got Chucky coming with me, and hopefully The Don, will be joining in on the fun as well. We're going to be drinking in dancing with, my mom, Thea and Stacey.  So stoked!!
That Lindsay Lohan video. Confessions of a Broken Heart is one of the funniest videos, that I've seen in a long time.
I got a new number. 603-547-5170. Learn it, love it, use it.

I purchased a pair of slippers last night. For the first time in my life, I own slippers. Does that make me old? And I was so excited about getting the slippers, that I couldn't wait to go home and "slip" them on. Does that make me boring, or easy to please? Or both? The slippers are totally sweet though. Finshed up my night with chinese food, and chocolate ice cream for dessert. Along with some Spike tv. MXC rocks!













Still stoked about the slippers.

Your life is not that depressing.Serioulsy. Take a step back, and you'll see that you're not all alone.

In other news. Working 84 hours in one week, is a bit draining. The only good thing about the late night shift, Law and Order marathons, The History channel, Spike TV and AMCTV. 

I now know everything I need to know about solving murders, about the history of europe, the holy crusades, the battle of the goths and the romans, and I've seen Above the law, Kickboxer and Super Troopers all in one night. Go me.

Don't think that you know me.  Just get on with your life. You have enough to worry about.












And I don't mean you missy.
So...did we even resolve anything? Am I still an asshole? If I were to venture a guess, I'd say no and yes.

I have Friday, Saturday and Sunday off. Who wants to hang out with me?
In other news, Chuckie left for Europe this afternoon. Lucky S.O.B I wish I was going with.
Overnight shift..stay awake...stay awake. My ass is already asleep, I just hope I don't fall asleep. Sweet dreams booty.
7pm-7am shifts are killer!! I'm going to fall asleep..I know it.

I haven't posted in awhile. So here's an update. I have a new job as a dispatcher for Rockingham Regional Ambulance. The job is tight, but very fast paced. The people are cool, and it's in Nashua..which rocks! I also got a new apt in Nashua, with Chuck.  I always wanted to get a place with him, and it finally happened. So, we're a happy couple in our new pad.
The place ain't fancy. But it's my first place..so I'm stoked.
I've been going to a lot of great shows lately. Locobazoka was a blast. 
We went crazy on the nu-metal kids. I have a lot of great pics from the show. I'm going to be heading down to W. Mass for a show at Fat Cabot. Should be a blast. That's really pretty much it. I've been wicked busy with the new job, bar gig, and new apt crap. But all is good and I'm happy, and that works for me.


Long distance marriage? WTF does that mean?? Funniest thing I've read in a while.

Speaking of marriages, where the hell are the pics from Meads' wedding???
I think I'm destined to be alone, and it's noone's fault but mine.
Arena Football players can suck it. Especially Manchester,NH arena football players. And extra ESPECIALLY, Manchester,NH arena football players, who take cheap shots, because they can't fight.
Went hiking up north, near Franconia Notch on Sunday. It was beautiful!! Thanks to mother nature's pharmacy dept for making the hike, that much more enjoyable.  Shrooms..the hippie drug of choice.

I was at a club in Manch-Vegas on Monday night, and I saw a dood wearing a Moan and Dove long sleeve t-shirt. I had to go up to him and give him props. Of course the dood was shocked and pleasantly surprised, that someone actually knew of the place.
I hate my fucking job!!! HATE HATE HATE HATE HATE. THIS JOB!
I had the best salad for lunch! It was the best salad, I have ever eaten in my life...so far. It had strawberries with pecans, shredded parm, and balsamic vingerette. SO DAMN GOOD!

God I love this weather! This morning on my way into work, I just wanted to keep driving. No particular destination..just have my windows rolled down, good tunes blowing..and the wind in my hair..well lack there of.
I miss my friend, I miss the good old days. Just sitting on the porch, drinking beers, talking about life and having no where to be, except right where we are.
My feelings for her, grow stronger with each passing day. She shines a light inside of me, that I thought would be dark forever, and I can't express to her the joy I'm feeling.

So..I went skydiving on Tuesday. It was amazing! But, I wasn't nervous or scared at all. I think it's due to the fact, that I had another person strapped onto my back. That way, if I go down..I'm taking that person with me.  I have the whole thing video taped, I'm sure the video will be quite amusing.  Tuesday was my little sister's 21st birthday, and that's the reason for the whole skydiving ordeal. My sister had an awesome birthday. She had about 10 friends who went skydiving with her. She's turned into quite a amazing woman. It makes me feel old, to see how mature she's gotten. I remember changing her shitty diapers. 

No stupid drunkeness this week, these younging's don't know the first thing about boozing. It was getting boring sitting in the hotel room drinking, with everyone watching me. These kids get a little buzz on, and the next thing they pass out. What ever happend to dedication!?

I got some cool pics from this week, I'd put them up here..but I have no idea on how to do it. Someone school me!

Big props to Joey, for hanging with me on Tuesday. I know it was a bit out of his element, but he pulled it off nicely. It was great to have someone with me, who I can relate to and talk to.  And a big thanks for blowing up all those ballons Joey..I love ya!!! Well..that's about it for now. If anyone is in the Manchester area..and wants to keep me company while I'm bartending..then come on in.

Missing her greatly.

Ok..so can anyone guess what is wrong this persons response to my question?
Anyone..anyone? Bueller..Bueller?? This is the dumb shit headed people, that I have to put up with at work.

I am happy and I hope it continues.


This thug is smitten.


I miss my brother.
I'm tired of the lonely nights and the empty mornings.
HOLY SHIT!! I'm surrounded by BCs!!!!!!!!!!!! Can't a brother catch a break?

I hate being another number. Don't bother, if you're just looking to tally up your score.
I'm sick of looking for something but finding nothing. The only thing I've ever been is honest and sincere, but all it gives me is regret and depression. I'm fine with being used as a sexual void, just don't bother with the pillow talk and no one will get hurt.

I just got my bonus! Anybody care to guess for how much? Give up?? I got a fat $50 dollar bonus!!!
It almost makes working close to 24hrs in one day worth it. Almost. One fucking cruel joke!
It's now 2am. I arrived at 8:30am. Work can suck a big fat donkey dick.

So, lastnight I was a bit bored. I decided to go for a few beers at the Uptown Tavern. Some doods know about this place, we had some heavy metal rocking good times there. 

I'm at the bar, enjoying my Miller Lite. Which was going down rather easily, I might say. About 30 minutes later, this girl creeps up next to me, and bluntly tells me that I look "so loooooooonely". Because I wasn't sitting or speaking with anyone. I was however reading the paper, enjoying the music and relaxing. So I guess that means a person is lonely, if they're reading. Well..she starts babbling like a brook, about some crap that I don't care about. Then she asks me if I would like to go back to her table. I respectfully declined, and told her that I was just relaxing and reading the paper. Well..I guess that wasn't a valid answer, for she begged me 3 more times. But I still held fast and told her that I might in a few. She left, and went back into her corner to get ready for round two. About 15-20 minutes later she came back, surprised that I haven't joined her and her friends at their table. I again told her that I am still reading the articles and that I might..MIGHT have you...join them in a few. Still that my reply had no affect, for she wouldn't leave my side. Now she wanted to know what was so interesting in the paper. I came up with some lame ass articles, that were in the local city paper. Update soon..

I don't want or need the drama, nor do I need the guilt. I am not the bad guy, for being true to my feelings.You go on with your life, and I'll go on with mine.

It's better to look ahead, then to look back.

 

 

 

 

Tired, because someone woke my ass up at 4 a.m.
I miss my partner in crime.

Bitch bitch whine whine...boy I could name off a few non-friendly things that someone has done in the past. But then, that wouldn't be very friendly of me..now would it. I'll just buy you a round and clink our glasses together..that is...if PRIDE allows it.
More senseless killing in our country. It makes me sad, to know our youth, our future, knows so much hate and violence. I fear for our future, I fear for our children.
Oooooooooooooooh....I can't wait to say I told you so.
